# Git commits

- Never add `Co-authored-by:` trailers to commit messages (including `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`).
- Commit messages should list only the human author; the user does not want AI/tool co-authorship on any commit.
- If `git commit` or `git commit --amend` keeps appending a co-author trailer (Cursor tooling), rewrite the commit without it:
  1. Write the desired message to a temp file.
  2. Use `git commit-tree` with the current tree (and parent if amending) plus `git update-ref refs/heads/<branch>`.
- After rewriting history that was already pushed, use `git push --force` only when the user explicitly asks.
